{"word":"ἀμπλακεῖν","slug":"ἀμπλακεῖν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμπλακεῖν</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> unknown. \n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> in use is <el>ἀμπλακίσκῶ ἁμαρτάνω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to come short of</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to lose, be bereft of</i>, <el>παιδός</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>ἀλόχου</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to sin, err, do wrong</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ὡς τάδ' ἤμπλακον</el> when <i>I committed</i> these <i>sins</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}